  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (114413c 2022-07-19T00:08:18.125698929Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test --fork-url $URL\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen running from a github action via ` onbjerg/foundry-toolchain@v1` . Foundry panics with the following error\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  Failed to get account for 0xb4c7â€¦7e84\r\nProviderError(SerdeJson { err: Error(\"EOF while parsing a value\", line: 1, column: 0), text: \"\" })\r\nLocation: evm/src/executor/fork/backend.rs:263\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe github action file for reference is:\r\n\r\n```\r\non: [push]\r\n\r\nname: Unit Tests\r\n\r\njobs:\r\n  check:\r\n    name: Foundry Tests\r\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\r\n    steps:\r\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v2\r\n        with:\r\n          submodules: recursive\r\n      - name: Install Foundry\r\n        uses: onbjerg/foundry-toolchain@v1\r\n        with:\r\n          version: nightly\r\n      - name: cli info\r\n        run: |\r\n          forge --version\r\n      - name: Run tests\r\n        run: make test\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Makefile\r\n```\r\n-include .env.ci\r\n.PHONY: all test clean\r\n\r\n# deps\r\ninstall:; forge install\r\nupdate:; forge update\r\n\r\n# Build & test\r\nbuild:; forge build\r\ntest:; forge test --fork-url $FILTERED_OUT_URL\r\ntrace:; forge test -vvv\r\nclean:; forge clean\r\nsnapshot:; forge snapshot\r\nfmt:; forge fmt\r\n```\r\n",
